    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/333.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s July 10, my July 5. Have taken matter up with Secretary Finance
                    Villareal, who informs me he has repeated his instructions to customs
                    authorities at Tampico, Tuxpam, and other gulf ports, to accept New York
                    exchange in lieu of Mexican gold at current rate of exchange, one for two.
                    Informed me decree issued in March made export duties, bar, and other port dues
                    payable in Mexican gold. I have informed Consul Miller, Tampico.</p>
                <p>Secretary Finance Villareal expects continuing his headquarters in Monterey.
                    General Carranza expected here soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
